just_use sse_notify.go

# label: SPIKE (ANCHOR_COMMENTS stack)
# role: Gopher view — Server-Sent Events stream + bell widget

Real-time notification channel so Steve's browser lights up
when Claude posts something (wiki reply, DM) without a page
reload. One SSE connection per open tab, multiplexed via
`notify.Subscribe`.

## Two exports

- `HandleSSEClaudeActivity(w, r)` — routed at
  `/gopher/sse/claude-activity`. Streams `notify.Event` JSON
  as SSE `activity` events. Browser holds this open for the
  lifetime of the tab.
- `NotificationWidget` — HTML+JS string constant. Injected
  into every page shell. Fixed top-right bell; hidden until
  an `activity` event fires; click "open →" navigates to the
  event's URL.

## Why SSE (not WebSocket)

One-way push from server → client is the only direction
needed. SSE is simpler: no handshake protocol, no
bidirectional framing, just a long-lived HTTP response that
`EventSource` consumes natively.

## Event shape (from `notify.Event`)

JSON with `sender`, `kind`, `summary`, `snippet`, `url`.
The widget renders `sender • kind` at the top, summary line,
snippet body, and an "open →" link. Dismiss is client-only
(closes the bell without side-effects).

## Pointers

- Publisher: `notify/` package — anywhere `notify.Publish(...)`
  fires, this stream emits.
- Part of: ANCHOR_COMMENTS stack
  (`project_anchor_comments_stack.md`).
- Injected by: page shell (`views/helpers.go` or similar) via
  `NotificationWidget` concatenation.
